com.nokia.mid.ui
Interface SoftNotificationListener

public interface SoftNotificationListener

SoftNotificationListener interface is used by applications which need callbacks from soft notifications. Listener will get a notification when the soft notification is either selected or dismissed by the user. Listener interface can be registered with SoftNotification.setListener(SoftNotificationListener) method This API is an optional feature in Nokia UI API, and depending on the device capabilities there may be implementations that do not support soft notifications. The System.getProperty("com.nokia.mid.ui.softnotification") will return "true" if this feature is available in the device.

Method Detail

notificationSelected

void notificationSelected(SoftNotification notification)
Indicates that a soft notification was selected by the user. The platform calls SoftNotification.remove() before notificationSelected() is called. Application that posted the soft notification is activated before the listener will get the notification.

Parameters:
notification - object identifying the soft notification being responded to by the user. The MIDlet must implement the functionality to be performed when the notification is selected.

notificationDismissed

void notificationDismissed(SoftNotification notification)
Indicates that a soft notification was dismissed by the user. The platform calls SoftNotification.remove() before notificationDismissed() is called.

Parameters:
notification - object identifying the soft notification being responded to by the user. The application must implement the functionality to be performed when the soft notification is dismissed, it is not required to do anything.
